{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:34:35.239Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the fundamental calculus formula that computes the derivative of a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "composite function"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (a function inside another function, like \"Russian nesting dolls\"). It's the mathematical backbone of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in neural networks, enabling efficient gradient computation through dozens of stacked layers by breaking down complex derivatives into simple local pieces."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Chain Rule тАФ concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is тАФ Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a composite function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "y = f(g(x))"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", the chain rule states:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "dy/dx = f'(g(x)) ┬╖ g'(x)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In words"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The derivative of the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "outer function"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (evaluated at the inner function) times the derivative of the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "inner function"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Alternative notation (more intuitive):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If y = f(u) and u = g(x), then:\ndy/dx = dy/du ├Ч du/dx"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Natural reading"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"The rate of change of y with respect to x equals the rate of change of y with respect to u, times the rate of change of u with respect to x\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual analogy тАФ Russian nesting dolls:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Function composition: y = f(g(x))\n\nThink of it like nested dolls:\n  Outer doll: f(u)\n  Inner doll: g(x)\n\nTo differentiate:\n1. Open outer doll тЖТ differentiate f(u) тЖТ get f'(u)\n2. Plug in inner function тЖТ f'(g(x))\n3. Open inner doll тЖТ differentiate g(x) тЖТ get g'(x)\n4. Multiply: f'(g(x)) ├Ч g'(x) [web:179]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Factory analogy:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Raw material тЖТ Machine A тЖТ Intermediate тЖТ Machine B тЖТ Final product\n\nChain rule: How does raw material change affect final product?\n= (effect of Machine A) ├Ч (effect of Machine B)\n= du/dx ├Ч dy/du [web:181]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters тАФ Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The chain rule is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "absolutely essential for machine learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML Component"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How chain rule applies"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computes gradients through neural network layers = chain rule applied recursively"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Neural Network Training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each layer is a function composition; chain rule differentiates through all layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss Minimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chain rule computes тИВLoss/тИВweight for millions of parameters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep Learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enables training networks with 100+ layers by decomposing derivatives"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In GPT training, the loss depends on the output, which depends on layer N, which depends on layer N-1,..., which depends on input. Chain rule computes тИВLoss/тИВweightтВБ by multiplying all these local derivatives."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits тАФ Key advantages"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "тЬЕ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Handles compositions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Differentiate functions you can't easily expand"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "тЬЕ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Local computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Break complex derivative into simple pieces"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "тЬЕ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Avoids expanding enormous composite expressions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "тЬЕ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer-by-layer"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Enables backpropagation through neural networks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "тЬЕ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Recursive"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Applies to any number of composed functions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs тАФ Downsides and limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-off"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Numerical instability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chain of multiplications can explode or vanish (gradient issues)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Order matters"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Must apply chain rule in correct order (outer тЖТ inner)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Complexity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Many layers тЖТ many chain rule applications тЖТ harder to debug"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works тАФ Step-by-step computation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single-variable chain rule:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "y = sin(x┬▓)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Identify outer and inner functions\n  Outer: f(u) = sin(u)\n  Inner: u = g(x) = x┬▓\n\nStep 2: Differentiate outer function\n  f'(u) = cos(u)\n  f'(g(x)) = cos(x┬▓)\n\nStep 3: Differentiate inner function\n  g'(x) = 2x\n\nStep 4: Multiply (chain rule)\n  dy/dx = cos(x┬▓) ├Ч 2x"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example 2"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "y = (3x + 2)тБ╡"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Identify functions\n  Outer: f(u) = uтБ╡\n  Inner: u = g(x) = 3x + 2\n\nStep 2: Differentiate outer\n  f'(u) = 5uтБ┤\n  f'(g(x)) = 5(3x + 2)тБ┤  тЖР Keep inner function!\n\nStep 3: Differentiate inner\n  g'(x) = 3\n\nStep 4: Multiply\n  dy/dx = 5(3x + 2)тБ┤ ├Ч 3 = 15(3x + 2)тБ┤"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistake тАФ Forgetting to plug back inner function:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WRONG: dy/dx = 5uтБ┤ ├Ч 3 = 15uтБ┤  тЖР u is not defined!\nCORRECT: dy/dx = 5(3x + 2)тБ┤ ├Ч 3 = 15(3x + 2)тБ┤  тЖР Plug in u = 3x + 2"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-variable chain rule (for neural networks):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Extended chain rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If y depends on u, which depends on v, which depends on x:\ndy/dx = dy/du ├Ч du/dv ├Ч dv/dx"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In neural network"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss L = f(wтВГ, wтВВ, wтВБ) where:\n  wтВГ depends on wтВВ\n  wтВВ depends on wтВБ\n\nтИВL/тИВwтВБ = тИВL/тИВwтВГ ├Ч тИВwтВГ/тИВwтВВ ├Ч тИВwтВВ/тИВwтВБ"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementations"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual computation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Function: y = sin(x┬▓)\ndef f(x):\n    return np.sin(x**2)\n\n# Derivative using chain rule: dy/dx = cos(x┬▓) ├Ч 2x\ndef derivative_chain_rule(x):\n    return np.cos(x**2) * 2 * x\n\n# Numerical verification\nx = 1.0\nh = 1e-5\nnumerical = (f(x + h) - f(x)) / h\nanalytical = derivative_chain_rule(x)\n\nprint(f\"Numerical: {numerical}\")      # тЙИ 0.909\nprint(f\"Analytical: {analytical}\")    # тЙИ 0.909 тЬУ"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch (autograd):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nx = torch.tensor([1.0], requires_grad=True)\ny = torch.sin(x**2)\n\n# Automatic chain rule application\ny.backward()\n\nprint(f\"Derivative: {x.grad}\")  # тЙИ 0.909 (matches chain rule)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chain Rule in Backpropagation тАФ The neural network application"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Neural network as function composition:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input x тЖТ Layer 1 тЖТ aтВБ тЖТ Layer 2 тЖТ aтВВ тЖТ ... тЖТ Layer N тЖТ Output тЖТ Loss\n\nMathematically:\n  aтВБ = fтВБ(x)\n  aтВВ = fтВВ(aтВБ) = fтВВ(fтВБ(x))\n  aтВГ = fтВГ(aтВВ) = fтВГ(fтВВ(fтВБ(x)))\n  ...\n  Loss = L(aтВЩ) = L(fтВЩ(fтВЩтВЛтВБ(...fтВБ(x)...)))\n\nThis is a COMPOSITION of functions! [web:180]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing тИВLoss/тИВweight via chain rule:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For weight w in layer 1:\n\nLoss depends on output aтВЩ\naтВЩ depends on aтВЩтВЛтВБ\naтВЩтВЛтВБ depends on aтВЩтВЛтВВ\n...\naтВВ depends on aтВБ\naтВБ depends on w\n\nтИВLoss/тИВw = тИВLoss/тИВaтВЩ ├Ч тИВaтВЩ/тИВaтВЩтВЛтВБ ├Ч тИВaтВЩтВЛтВБ/тИВaтВЩтВЛтВВ ├Ч ... ├Ч тИВaтВВ/тИВaтВБ ├Ч тИВaтВБ/тИВw"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Each term is a \"local derivative\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " тАФ easy to compute!"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-step backpropagation example:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Simple 2-layer neural network\n# Input тЖТ Layer 1 (wтВБ) тЖТ Activation тЖТ Layer 2 (wтВВ) тЖТ Output тЖТ Loss\n\n# Parameters\nw1 = 0.5\nw2 = 1.0\n\n# Input and target\nx = 2.0\ny_true = 3.0\n\n# Forward pass\na1 = w1 * x                 # Layer 1 output\na2 = np.tanh(a1)            # Activation\noutput = w2 * a2            # Layer 2 output\nloss = (output - y_true)**2 # MSE loss\n\nprint(f\"Loss: {loss:.4f}\")  # тЙИ 0.25\n\n# Backward pass (chain rule!)\n# Compute тИВLoss/тИВw1\n\n# Step 1: тИВLoss/тИВoutput = 2(output - y_true)\ndLoss_dOutput = 2 * (output - y_true)\n\n# Step 2: тИВoutput/тИВw2 = a2\ndOutput_dW2 = a2\n\n# Step 3: тИВoutput/тИВa2 = w2\ndOutput_da2 = w2\n\n# Step 4: тИВa2/тИВa1 = 1 - tanh┬▓(a1) (derivative of tanh)\nda2_da1 = 1 - np.tanh(a1)**2\n\n# Step 5: тИВa1/тИВw1 = x\nda1_dW1 = x\n\n# CHAIN RULE: Multiply all local derivatives\ndLoss_dW1 = dLoss_dOutput * dOutput_da2 * da2_da1 * da1_dW1\ndLoss_dW2 = dLoss_dOutput * dOutput_dW2\n\nprint(f\"тИВLoss/тИВw1: {dLoss_dW1:.4f}\")  # тЙИ -1.5\nprint(f\"тИВLoss/тИВw2: {dLoss_dW2:.4f}\")  # тЙИ -0.25"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule flow"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss тЖТ output тЖТ aтВВ тЖТ aтВБ тЖТ wтВБ\n  тИВL/тИВwтВБ = тИВL/тИВoutput ├Ч тИВoutput/тИВaтВВ ├Ч тИВaтВВ/тИВaтВБ ├Ч тИВaтВБ/тИВwтВБ"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key formulas тАФ Chain rule variations"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single variable:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "dy/dx = dy/du ├Ч du/dx"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-variable (partial derivatives):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "тИВz/тИВx = тИВz/тИВu ├Ч тИВu/тИВx + тИВz/тИВv ├Ч тИВv/тИВx"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where z = f(u, v) and u, v depend on x"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extended chain (multiple layers):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "dy/dx = dy/duтВБ ├Ч duтВБ/duтВВ ├Ч duтВВ/duтВГ ├Ч ... ├Ч duтВЩ/dx"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes тАФ Pitfalls to avoid"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correction"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not plugging back inner function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f'(g(x)) must have g(x) inside, not just u"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Wrong order"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always: outer derivative ├Ч inner derivative"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forgetting chain rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For composite functions, MUST use chain rule (not just product/sum rule)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Manual computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use autograd for neural networks"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices тАФ Proven approaches"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Use autograd frameworks"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nmodel = NeuralNetwork()\nloss = compute_loss(model(x), y)\n\n# Chain rule automatically applied in backpropagation\nloss.backward()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Check gradient flow"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Monitor for gradient vanishing/explosion\nfor name, param in model.named_parameters():\n    if param.grad is not None:\n        grad_norm = param.grad.norm()\n        print(f\"{name}: gradient norm = {grad_norm:.4f}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Use activation functions with good gradients"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# ReLU avoids vanishing gradient (derivative = 1 for positive inputs)\nactivation = torch.nn.ReLU()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule = derivative of composite function"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": dy/dx = dy/du ├Ч du/dx"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outer ├Ч inner"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Derivative of outer function (at inner) ├Ч derivative of inner"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Russian nesting dolls"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Differentiate outer layer, then inner layer, multiply"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation = chain rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Neural network training applies chain rule recursively"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Local derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Break complex derivative into simple pieces multiplied together"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Extended chain"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": dy/dx = dy/duтВБ ├Ч duтВБ/duтВВ ├Ч... ├Ч duтВЩ/dx"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Don't forget inner function"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": f'(g(x)) must keep g(x) inside"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Essential for deep learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Enables training 100+ layer networks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use autograd"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": PyTorch/TensorFlow apply chain rule automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, the chain rule is the mathematical foundation that makes neural networks trainable: every backpropagation step, every gradient computation, and every weight update relies on the chain rule to decompose the derivative of the loss with respect to millions/billions of parameters into a product of simple local derivatives."}]}]}}